Draw a random sample from an F distribution

Source: R/FisherF.R
random.FisherF.Rd

Draw a random sample from an F distribution

# S3 method for FisherF
random(d, n = 1L, ...)

Arguments

d

A FisherF object created by a call to FisherF().
n

The number of samples to draw. Defaults to 1L.
...

Unused. Unevaluated arguments will generate a warning to catch mispellings or other possible errors.

Value

A numeric vector of length n.

Examples


X <- FisherF(5, 10, 0.2)
X

random(X, 10)
#>  [1] 1.6397528 0.9719911 0.4729643 0.4774881 0.3986624 0.7230272 1.1658319
#>  [8] 0.4773739 1.0330502 0.7308697

pdf(X, 2)
#> [1] 0.1699603
log_pdf(X, 2)
#> [1] -1.77219

cdf(X, 4)
#> [1] 0.9667464
quantile(X, 0.7)
#> [1] 1.467954

cdf(X, quantile(X, 0.7))
#> [1] 0.7
quantile(X, cdf(X, 7))
#> [1] 7
